page.title: 07THE VICARAGE
page.content: The vicarage is a very interesting building.It is about 145 years old.The present vicar is the Reverend Degg and he has lived here for about 7 years. The vicarage now has ten rooms but centuries ago there were many more rooms.Only two people live in the vicarage now plus a very big dog. Outside, the old coach house and stables have been changed.Extensions to the vicarage have been made and windows have been altered. The vicarage is not next to the church because the people who built it did not own the land next to the church,so it is a short walk away. In October 1985 the Rev.Degg will be having a very important visitor to the vicarage,the Bishop of Birmingham.
